Maximum sum of an subarray
input: [2,3,-8,7,-1,2,3]
output: 11

explaination: sum of 7,-1,2 and 3 is 11

Logic:
if inbetween cause negative than before then remove those anyway no use to add in array.
kadanes algorithm, check the current sum , if its neagtive reset it with current index place -  sum = Math.max(arr[i],sum+arr[i]);
find max by adding each with existing max

class Solution {
    int maxSubarraySum(int[] arr) {
        // Code here
        int maxSum=arr[0];
        int sum=arr[0];
        for (int i=1; i<arr.length; i++){
            sum = Math.max(arr[i],sum+arr[i]);
            
            maxSum= Math.max(maxSum,sum);
            
        }
        return maxSum;
        
    }
}
